## This package contains driver and controller for controlling Lambda7 haptic device.

## Prequisites
    -   CHAI3D
    -   hiredis  (sudo apt install libhiredis-dev)
    -   Eigen
    -   redis-server

Before building, please change the redis_client_remote ip address (if using two machines).

## Build instructions.

1. change the "CHAI3D" build path in CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH expression to your own CHAI3D build path.

2. Navigate to "build" folder and build the project. The binary files will stored in "/bin" folder.

3. commands are as follows
    $ cmake ..
    $ make 

## Executing the program

1. open a terminal, navigate to bin folder and run "chai_haptics_redis_driver" first.
2. Ensure to change redis.conf so that redis_server can be exposed to internet.
   Change the remote redis client ip and build the project again.
3. Open a new terminal and execute the haptic_controller program.
